arguments.prompt:
You are implementing features for a Blazor Web App (Interactive Auto, Global mode with Individual auth) located at `/tmp/sv-f139feb5f52a4e57ba4da161acac2a26/ShipmentTracker/`. The solution has two projects:
- `ShipmentTracker` (server) 
- `ShipmentTracker.Client` (WebAssembly)

The app is for a logistics company tracking shipments. Requirements:
- Dispatchers view a list of shipments with status and destination
- Customers check their shipment status and estimated delivery
- Users authenticate with individual accounts (already scaffolded)

## Architecture (Auto mode rules)
- All interactive components MUST go in the `.Client` project
- No direct DB access from `.Client` components — use HTTP APIs
- Define service interfaces in `.Client`, implement with HttpClient there
- Server implements same interfaces with EF Core for prerendering
- Register matching services in both Program.cs files
- Expose server data through minimal API endpoints

## What to implement

### 1. Shared Models — Create in `.Client` project

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Models/Shipment.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

public class Shipment
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string TrackingNumber { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Origin { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Destination { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public ShipmentStatus Status { get; set; }
    public DateTime CreatedAt { get; set; }
    public DateTime? EstimatedDelivery { get; set; }
    public string CustomerEmail { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Description { get; set; } = string.Empty;
}

public enum ShipmentStatus
{
    Pending,
    PickedUp,
    InTransit,
    OutForDelivery,
    Delivered,
    Delayed
}
```

### 2. Service Interface — Create in `.Client` project

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/IShipmentService.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

public interface IShipmentService
{
    Task<List<Shipment>> GetAllShipmentsAsync();
    Task<Shipment?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber);
    Task<List<Shipment>> GetShipmentsByCustomerAsync(string customerEmail);
    Task<Shipment> CreateShipmentAsync(Shipment shipment);
    Task UpdateShipmentStatusAsync(int id, ShipmentStatus status);
}
```

### 3. Client-side HttpClient implementation

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/ShipmentServiceClient.cs`:
```csharp
using System.Net.Http.Json;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

public class ShipmentServiceClient(HttpClient http) : IShipmentService
{
    public async Task<List<Shipment>> GetAllShipmentsAsync()
    {
        return await http.GetFromJsonAsync<List<Shipment>>("api/shipments") ?? [];
    }

    public async Task<Shipment?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber)
    {
        return await http.GetFromJsonAsync<Shipment?>($"api/shipments/track/{trackingNumber}");
    }

    public async Task<List<Shipment>> GetShipmentsByCustomerAsync(string customerEmail)
    {
        return await http.GetFromJsonAsync<List<Shipment>>($"api/shipments/customer/{Uri.EscapeDataString(customerEmail)}") ?? [];
    }

    public async Task<Shipment> CreateShipmentAsync(Shipment shipment)
    {
        var response = await http.PostAsJsonAsync("api/shipments", shipment);
        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();
        return await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<Shipment>() ?? shipment;
    }

    public async Task UpdateShipmentStatusAsync(int id, ShipmentStatus status)
    {
        var response = await http.PutAsJsonAsync($"api/shipments/{id}/status", status);
        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();
    }
}
```

### 4. Server-side EF Core implementation

First, add a `Shipment` entity to the server DB. Create `ShipmentTracker/Data/ShipmentEntity.cs`:
```csharp
using System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Data;

public class ShipmentEntity
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    [MaxLength(50)]
    public string TrackingNumber { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    [MaxLength(200)]
    public string Origin { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    [MaxLength(200)]
    public string Destination { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public int Status { get; set; }
    public DateTime CreatedAt { get; set; }
    public DateTime? EstimatedDelivery { get; set; }
    [MaxLength(256)]
    public string CustomerEmail { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    [MaxLength(500)]
    public string Description { get; set; } = string.Empty;
}
```

Add a `DbSet<ShipmentEntity>` to the existing `ApplicationDbContext`. The file is at `ShipmentTracker/Data/ApplicationDbContext.cs`. Add:
```csharp
public DbSet<ShipmentEntity> Shipments => Set<ShipmentEntity>();
```

Then create `ShipmentTracker/Services/ShipmentServiceServer.cs`:
```csharp
using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;
using ShipmentTracker.Data;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Services;

public class ShipmentServiceServer(IDbContextFactory<ApplicationDbContext> contextFactory) : IShipmentService
{
    public async Task<List<Shipment>> GetAllShipmentsAsync()
    {
        await using var context = await contextFactory.CreateDbContextAsync();
        return await context.Shipments
            .OrderByDescending(s => s.CreatedAt)
            .Select(s => MapToModel(s))
            .ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Shipment?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber)
    {
        await using var context = await contextFactory.CreateDbContextAsync();
        var entity = await context.Shipments
            .FirstOrDefaultAsync(s => s.TrackingNumber == trackingNumber);
        return entity is null ? null : MapToModel(entity);
    }

    public async Task<List<Shipment>> GetShipmentsByCustomerAsync(string customerEmail)
    {
        await using var context = await contextFactory.CreateDbContextAsync();
        return await context.Shipments
            .Where(s => s.CustomerEmail == customerEmail)
            .OrderByDescending(s => s.CreatedAt)
            .Select(s => MapToModel(s))
            .ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Shipment> CreateShipmentAsync(Shipment shipment)
    {
        await using var context = await contextFactory.CreateDbContextAsync();
        var entity = new ShipmentEntity
        {
            TrackingNumber = shipment.TrackingNumber,
            Origin = shipment.Origin,
            Destination = shipment.Destination,
            Status = (int)shipment.Status,
            CreatedAt = DateTime.UtcNow,
            EstimatedDelivery = shipment.EstimatedDelivery,
            CustomerEmail = shipment.CustomerEmail,
            Description = shipment.Description
        };
        context.Shipments.Add(entity);
        await context.SaveChangesAsync();
        shipment.Id = entity.Id;
        shipment.CreatedAt = entity.CreatedAt;
        return shipment;
    }

    public async Task UpdateShipmentStatusAsync(int id, ShipmentStatus status)
    {
        await using var context = await contextFactory.CreateDbContextAsync();
        var entity = await context.Shipments.FindAsync(id);
        if (entity is not null)
        {
            entity.Status = (int)status;
            await context.SaveChangesAsync();
        }
    }

    private static Shipment MapToModel(ShipmentEntity entity) => new()
    {
        Id = entity.Id,
        TrackingNumber = entity.TrackingNumber,
        Origin = entity.Origin,
        Destination = entity.Destination,
        Status = (ShipmentStatus)entity.Status,
        CreatedAt = entity.CreatedAt,
        EstimatedDelivery = entity.EstimatedDelivery,
        CustomerEmail = entity.CustomerEmail,
        Description = entity.Description
    };
}
```

### 5. Update ApplicationDbContext

The file is at `ShipmentTracker/Data/ApplicationDbContext.cs`. Add `public DbSet<ShipmentEntity> Shipments => Set<ShipmentEntity>();` to the class.

### 6. Change AddDbContext to AddDbContextFactory

In the server `Program.cs` at `/tmp/sv-f139feb5f52a4e57ba4da161acac2a26/ShipmentTracker/ShipmentTracker/Program.cs`, change:
```csharp
builder.Services.AddDbContext<ApplicationDbContext>(options =>
    options.UseSqlite(connectionString));
```
to:
```csharp
builder.Services.AddDbContextFactory<ApplicationDbContext>(options =>
    options.UseSqlite(connectionString));
builder.Services.AddScoped<ApplicationDbContext>(sp =>
    sp.GetRequiredService<IDbContextFactory<ApplicationDbContext>>().CreateDbContext());
```

Also register the shipment service and HttpClient in the server `Program.cs`. Add these lines BEFORE `var app = builder.Build();`:
```csharp
builder.Services.AddScoped<IShipmentService, ShipmentServiceServer>();
builder.Services.AddHttpClient();
```

Add at the top of server Program.cs:
```csharp
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;
using ShipmentTracker.Services;
```

### 7. API Endpoints

Add minimal API endpoints in the server `Program.cs` BEFORE `app.Run();` but after `app.MapAdditionalIdentityEndpoints();`:

```csharp
// Shipment API endpoints
var shipments = app.MapGroup("api/shipments").RequireAuthorization();

shipments.MapGet("/", async (IShipmentService service) =>
    Results.Ok(await service.GetAllShipmentsAsync()));

shipments.MapGet("/track/{trackingNumber}", async (string trackingNumber, IShipmentService service) =>
{
    var shipment = await service.GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(trackingNumber);
    return shipment is not null ? Results.Ok(shipment) : Results.NotFound();
});

shipments.MapGet("/customer/{email}", async (string email, IShipmentService service) =>
    Results.Ok(await service.GetShipmentsByCustomerAsync(email)));

shipments.MapPost("/", async (Shipment shipment, IShipmentService service) =>
{
    var created = await service.CreateShipmentAsync(shipment);
    return Results.Created($"api/shipments/track/{created.TrackingNumber}", created);
});

shipments.MapPut("/{id}/status", async (int id, ShipmentStatus status, IShipmentService service) =>
{
    await service.UpdateShipmentStatusAsync(id, status);
    return Results.NoContent();
});
```

Add `using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;` to the top of server Program.cs.

### 8. Update Client Program.cs

In `/tmp/sv-f139feb5f52a4e57ba4da161acac2a26/ShipmentTracker/ShipmentTracker.Client/Program.cs`, register the HttpClient and shipment service:

```csharp
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.WebAssembly.Hosting;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

var builder = WebAssemblyHostBuilder.CreateDefault(args);

builder.Services.AddAuthorizationCore();
builder.Services.AddCascadingAuthenticationState();
builder.Services.AddAuthenticationStateDeserialization();

builder.Services.AddScoped(sp => new HttpClient { BaseAddress = new Uri(builder.HostEnvironment.BaseAddress) });
builder.Services.AddScoped<IShipmentService, ShipmentServiceClient>();

await builder.Build().RunAsync();
```

### 9. Pages — Dispatcher Dashboard

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Pages/Dispatcher.razor`:
```razor
@page "/dispatcher"
@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization
@using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models
@using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services
@attribute [Authorize]
@inject IShipmentService ShipmentService

<PageTitle>Dispatcher Dashboard</PageTitle>

<h1>Shipment Dashboard</h1>

<div class="mb-3 row">
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <input type="text" class="form-control" placeholder="Filter by destination..."
               @bind="filterText" @bind:event="oninput" />
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-3">
        <select class="form-select" @bind="statusFilter">
            <option value="">All Statuses</option>
            @foreach (var status in Enum.GetValues<ShipmentStatus>())
            {
                <option value="@status">@status</option>
            }
        </select>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-2">
        <button class="btn btn-primary" @onclick="LoadShipments">Refresh</button>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-3">
        <button class="btn btn-success" @onclick="ShowCreateForm">+ New Shipment</button>
    </div>
</div>

@if (showCreateForm)
{
    <div class="card mb-3">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">Create New Shipment</h5>
